1.clone existing repository
   git clone <url>
   e.g. git clone git@github.com:ssdut-0515/webdemo.git
2. show changes
   > git diff (show all tracked files changes with details)
   > git diff --name-only (only show all changed file names)
   > git diff --name-only . (show all changed file names under current directory)
3. show file status
   > git status . (show file status under current directory)
4. add file to index
   > git add <file> (add <file> to indices for committing)
   > git add -A . (add all changed and untracked files to indixes for commiting under current directory)

